objects.name: Qakbot Malware
objects.description: Qakbot, which originally started as a banking trojan in 2007, is a modular piece of malware which commonly operates as an information stealer. Used by multiple threat actors and groups, Qakbot can be used to deliver additional pay loads, reconnaissance, lateral movement, and gathering and exfiltrating data.
